p 3: Update `.env.example`\n\nAdd auth section with comments:\n\n```env\n# === Supabase Auth (SEC-01) ===\n# JWT secret for verifying Supabase-issued access tokens (HS256)\n# Get from: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API > JWT Settings\nSUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret\n# Service role key — bypasses RLS, used by background jobs (scrape/enrich/aggregate)\n# Get from: Supabase Dashboard > Project Settings > API > service_role key\nSUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key\n# Set to true ONLY in test environments to bypass auth middleware\nAUTH_DISABLED=false\n```\n\n**File:** `.env.example`\n\n### Step 4: Create `docs/runbooks/supabase-auth-setup.md`\n\nDocument:\n- Dashboard configuration steps (what was done and where)\n- Redirect URL list with instructions for adding new environments\n- 1Password item names for secret retrieval\n- JWT secret rotation procedure\n- Verification checklist (how to confirm auth is configured correctly)\n- Link to next issues (#207, #208, #209) in the auth chain\n\n**File:** `docs/runbooks/supabase-auth-setup.md` (new)\n\n### Step 5: Add test for production safety guard\n\nAdd a test in `tests/test_config.py` (or `tests/test_auth_config.py` if new file):\n\n```python\ndef test_auth_disabled_blocked_in_production():\n    \"\"\"AUTH_DISABLED=true must fail when ENVIRONMENT=production.\"\"\"\n    with pytest.raises(ValidationError, match=\"AUTH_DISABLED.*forbidden\"):\n        Settings(DATABASE_PASSWORD=\"x\", AUTH_DISABLED=True, ENVIRONMENT=\"production\")\n\ndef test_auth_disabled_allowed_in_dev():\n    \"\"\"AUTH_DISABLED=true is fine in dev/test.\"\"\"\n    s = Settings(DATABASE_PASSWORD=\"x\", AUTH_DISABLED=True, ENVIRONMENT=\"dev\")\n    assert s.AUTH_DISABLED is True\n```\n\n**File:** `tests/test_auth_config.py` (new, small)\n\n### Step 6: Verify & Commit\n\n```bash\nuv run ruff check src/ tests/ --fix && uv run ruff format src/ tests/\nuv run mypy src/compgraph/config.py\nuv run pytest -x -q --tb=short -m \"not inte